What you need to know:

After she retired from competition, she worked as a physical education teacher, and became head coach of the Israeli national gymnastics team.She was only able to return home to then-communist Hungary -- where she has lived since 2015 -- for the World Athletics championships in 1983."It was worth doing something well in life, considering the attention I have received, I get the shivers when I see all the articles written about me," Keleti says.